# A self-feeding structural cycle where each level of recursion also
# receives fresh struct conjuncts, e.g. `b: a, a: b: b: a` with `a`
# embedded at the top level, used to hang the evaluator: the "new depth
# implies no cycle" escape in detectCycle fired at every level, so the
# cycle was never marked and unify kept descending forever.
# https://cuelang.org/issue/4231
-- in.cue --
b: a
a: b: b: a
a

@test(err, code=structural_cycle, contains="structural cycle", pos=[])
-- out/errors.txt --
[structural_cycle] b.b.b.b.b.b: structural cycle
[structural_cycle] a.b.b: structural cycle
-- out/eval/stats --
